<Section id="problem" background="gray">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
    <h2 class="mb-6">The Problem with Traditional Fractional Sales</h2>

    <div class="text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-700 space-y-4">
      <p>Most startups hire a fractional sales leader. They get a playbook. Maybe some training.</p>
      <p>Then the engagement ends.</p>
      <p>The playbook sits in a Google Doc. Reps forget the messaging. New hires start from scratch. The founder ends up back in every deal.</p>

      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">
        You paid for expertise that walked out the door.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Section>
